    <note>Xu(4) Zhong [18713] The Leping Xu(4) seem to have been a diffuse lineage. Zhong [18713], Shan [18714] and Yin [796] all have mingzi that have similarities not uncommon in some systems of generational indicators. I am going to use Zhong as the point of departure as the first Song Leping Xu(4) jinshi and make Shan and Yin cousins and Gangzong [18715] a lineage (third) cousin, Bingqing [18716] a lineage (third) nephew of Ganzong and the two early 13th century Xu(4), who use radical 170 as a generational indicator, as great grandnephews of Zhong. I am not including the other Leping Xu(4). Jiangxi TZ, 21.31a. CBD, 3, 2152.</note>
